### 6. IMAP ObjectID Bis & Extensions Suggestions
* **Drafts:** 
  * [draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-objectid-bis](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-objectid-bis/)
  * [draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-extensions-suggestions](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-extensions-suggestions/)
* **Presenters:** Bron Gondwana, Mario Loffredo, and Ricardo Signes.
* **Discussion:**
  * **Flag Consistency:** Bron Gondwana discussed the challenge of handling IMAP flags across multiple copies of the same email. He agreed with Matt (on-list) that for JMAP/IMAP interoperability, all copies of a message sharing the same Email ID must expose identical flags, shifting the implementation complexity to the server.
  * **Implementation Status:** Cyrus IMAP already implements the server-side changes. Because the response format has changed, client-side implementations are required before advancing the draft. Arnt Gulbrandsen and Bron Gondwana (via a JMAP proxy) indicated immediate plans to work on client-side implementations.
  * **Extensions Suggestions:** Ricardo Signes reported that [draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-extensions-suggestions](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-extensions-suggestions/) is currently parked waiting for the completion of [draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-objectid-bis](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-objectid-bis/).

